This paper deals with facial expression recognition in video sequences, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves training a model to predict facial expressions on-the-fly, which requires real-time processing and could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of affective interactive agents, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
